Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, the Presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), on Sunday mourned late political activist, Stanley Nwabia. In a tweet, he personally signed, Atiku said Nwabia’s death was sobering. He tweeted: “It is a cause for sobering emotions to read about the sudden demise of @MrStanleyNwabia. A patriotic Nigerian and forthright supporter of our great party. God Almighty console his family and may his soul Rest In Peace – AA.” Nwabia is one of the well known social activists on social media, especially Twitter, where the news of his death has been trending. 